<subSubSection box="[197,1029,714,740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,964]" box="[197,1029,714,740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,337,714,740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Greek 
<taxonomicName box="[538,642,715,740]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agraulus">
<emphasis box="[538,642,715,740]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">agraulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning “living in field; farm”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,964]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,323,752,778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the key of 
<bibRefCitation box="[637,926,752,778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refString="Negrobov, O. P., Tsurikov, M. N. &amp; Maslova, O. O. (2000) Revision of the Palaearctic species of the genus Chrysotus Meigen. (Diptera, Dolichopodidae), III. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 79, 227 - 238." type="journal article">
Negrobov 
<emphasis box="[768,831,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[850,917,752,778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the new species will run to 
<taxonomicName authority="Negrobov et Maslova, 1995" authorityName="Negrobov et Maslova" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudisetus">
<emphasis box="[1283,1436,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. nudisetus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Negrobov" box="[151,483,789,815]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refString="Negrobov, O. P. &amp; Maslova, O. O. (1995) Revision of Palaearctic species of the genus Chrysotus Meigen (Diptera, Dolichopodidae), II. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 74, 456 - 466." type="journal article" year="1995">
Negrobov 
<emphasis box="[276,297,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et</emphasis>
Maslova, 
<number box="[422,483,789,815]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter by the very large ventral projection of the epandrium, with end flat and wide, and stands at level of distal margin of lateral epandrial lobe; hypandrium with ventral process pointed apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,964]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Based on the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Becker" box="[449,627,901,927]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refString="Becker, T. (1922 b) Dipterologische Studien. Dolichopodidae der Indo-Australischen Region. Capita Zoologica, 1, 1 - 247." type="journal article" year="1922">
Becker (
<number box="[553,619,901,927]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1922.0">1922</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the new species will run to couplet 
<number box="[1076,1093,901,927]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="3.0">3</number>
, but differs from all species under the couplet by blackish brown femora and yellow tibiae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
